commit.message: Update version for 0.3.0 final.
Include LICENSE files in source jar (at user request).
Upgrade optional (non-transitive) log4j dependency to version past apocalyptic bug. (Thanks @swyrik!)
When possible include given sql state in converted SQLException. (Thanks @eugeneRover!)
Relicense to let users choose later versions of LGPL.
Update build for sbt 1.9.8.
Have timestamp-emitting code generators support SOURCE_DATE_EPOCH for deterministic builds.
Delete trailing whitespace.
Add getStackTraces() method to ThreadPoolReportingAsynchronousRunner.
Define ThreadPoolReportingAsynchronousRunner interface, and let ThreadPoolAsynchronousRunner implement that.
Bump version to 0.3.0-SNAPSHOT, legacy support form Java 1.6 to Java 1.7
Update version for mchange-commons-java 0.2.20-final
In BoundedExecutorService acquire permits within task thread rather than upon task preparation.
Add a perfunctory paradox-based docsite and updateSite task.
Update version number for 0.2.19 final.
Implement RedirectableMLogger and stitch it into MLog as a configurable option, so that already in-use loggers can be redirected via forceMLog().
Enhancements to FallbackMLog, log logger names, accept filters.
Update clients of VersionsUtils to use new, less ambiguous API.
Update VersionUtils to correctly parse versions from newer JVMs. Make API less ambiguous between e.g. Java 1.0 and Java 10.
Update build for sbt 1.2.8
Update version for 0.2.18 final.
Add a hook so that subclasses of log4j2.MLogAppender can customize how the message is formatted.
Update version numbers for 0.2.17 final.
Define (experimental) MLogAppender bridge between log4j2 and MLog logging.
Add method to force use of FallbackMLog (as a convenience, see messages without configuration).
Update version for mchange-commons-java 0.2.17-SNAPSHOT, fix a bad apostrophe in a message.
Update version number to 0.2.16 final.
Eliminate unsupported Level.FINE reference mistakenly introduced in to Log4j2MLog
Let full-JVM-stack-trace dumps for ThreadPoolAsynchronousRunner be at FINER rather than FINE.
Define logging levels more consistently across implementations.
